<item>
            <title>[FLINK-4441] RocksDB statebackend makes all operators appear stateful</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4441</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the state is empty the rocks db state backend returns an empty hashmap instead of a null in the snapshotPartitionedState method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This means that these operators always appear stateful to the flink runtime which makes it impossible for instance to remove a stateless operator using the savepoints.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
